This quick start uses the live demo guide as an example.

You can open the demo here:  
https://docsassemblerdemo.netoftrees.com/?~u51rKe01DX~u5gpCU01mT-s7SMNM1VG

All content lives in ordinary Git repositories that you control completely. There are no subscriptions and no vendor lock-in.

The extension is free. You can publish guides to GitHub Pages or any static hosting you choose.

Other people can publish their own guides and make them available as remote guides. You include those remote guides in yours, and the third party keeps responsibility for updating their content and those changes will appear seamlessly within yours.

